the musicologist charles burney later took serse to task for violating decorum in this way , writing : " i have not been able to discover the author of the words of this drama : but it is one of the worst handel ever set to music : for besides feeble writing , there is a mixture of tragic - comedy and buffoonery in it , which apostolo zeno and metastasio had banished from serious opera."best p.15

